01:18:03,200 --> 01:18:05,300
You're a liar like all the rest.

761
01:18:05,400 --> 01:18:08,300
You made out you're some
kind of a hero, but you're nothing.

762
01:18:08,500 --> 01:18:10,000
You're worse than nothing.

763
01:18:10,300 --> 01:18:11,700
It's a job, man.

764
01:18:12,500 --> 01:18:17,300
Stop lying. Like you could ever
adopt one of us.

765
01:18:17,400 --> 01:18:20,800
Like you've got the right
to be our father.

766
01:18:21,000 --> 01:18:23,500
You're a nobody.
We don't need you.

767
01:18:23,700 --> 01:18:25,400
- Maps...
- We don't need anyone.

768
01:18:28,300 --> 01:18:29,700
Maps.

769
01:18:29,900 --> 01:18:31,200
Do you want a lift home?

770
01:18:31,400 --> 01:18:33,300
FOREMAN:
Clive!

771
01:18:34,300 --> 01:18:37,400
Get your ass back here now.

772
01:18:47,800 --> 01:18:50,000
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

773
01:18:58,800 --> 01:19:01,200
BAND Y:
Where have you been?

774
01:19:03,300 --> 01:19:05,900
MAPS: Where's the others?
- Looking for you.

775
01:19:07,600 --> 01:19:09,600
MRS. McANSH:
We've been worried about you.

776
01:19:10,400 --> 01:19:12,800
You must let us know
where you are, son.

777
01:19:16,500 --> 01:19:17,600
Son?

778
01:19:58,600 --> 01:20:00,000
What are you doing?

779
01:20:04,800 --> 01:20:06,300
Get your things. Now.

780
01:20:06,500 --> 01:20:09,500
We're leaving. Come on!

781
01:20:10,200 --> 01:20:11,900
- Get your stuff.
- Where are we going?

782
01:20:12,100 --> 01:20:14,900
MAPS:
Home. It's all been a lie.

783
01:20:18,500 --> 01:20:22,100
- Just shut up and get your stuff!
MISTY: Stop!

784
01:20:22,200 --> 01:20:24,400
[BOTH GRUNTING]

785
01:20:27,800 --> 01:20:29,300
MAPS:
Misty, get off!

786
01:20:40,200 --> 01:20:43,000
I'm trying to look after you!

787
01:21:14,900 --> 01:21:16,300
Nice spot you got here.

788
01:21:23,700 --> 01:21:25,000
Shit.

789
01:21:25,500 --> 01:21:28,000
The little bloke do that?

790
01:21:29,100 --> 01:21:31,800
You guys fight worse than brothers.

791
01:21:32,300 --> 01:21:34,200
We are brothers.

792
01:21:35,300 --> 01:21:39,100
Leave me alone. I'll be all right.

793
01:21:39,600 --> 01:21:42,000
Yeah, I don't doubt that.

794
01:21:42,500 --> 01:21:43,700
What about the others?

795
01:21:44,700 --> 01:21:47,500
You just gonna abandon them
because you're mad at Lucy?

796
01:21:47,700 --> 01:21:50,100
You don't know anything about it.

797
01:21:54,200 --> 01:21:57,200
Well, at least there's something
that I do know.

798
01:21:58,200 --> 01:22:01,200
You're wrong what you said to me.

799
01:22:02,200 --> 01:22:04,900
Teresa and me
would make good parents.

800
01:22:05,100 --> 01:22:08,700
And we would've had a load of kids
around now if it weren't for me.

801
01:22:09,200 --> 01:22:12,200
I crashed the bike
with Tess on the back.

802
01:22:13,700 --> 01:22:16,700
We used to be a team in the shows.

803
01:22:19,200 --> 01:22:22,200
She spent half a year in hospital.

804
01:22:24,500 --> 01:22:27,600
And I tried to keep it going
on my own, but...

805
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:34,600
Does Teresa know?

806
01:22:36,600 --> 01:22:38,900
Tess always knows.

807
01:22:47,100 --> 01:22:49,000
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

808
01:22:57,000 --> 01:22:59,200
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

809
01:23:41,000 --> 01:23:43,100
[THUNDER CRASHING]

810
01:23:44,300 --> 01:23:46,000
[HORSE NEIGHING]

811
01:23:48,400 --> 01:23:49,500
SPIT:
Help!

812
01:23:55,000 --> 01:23:57,300
Help me!

813
01:23:57,900 --> 01:24:00,000
Maps!

814
01:24:00,900 --> 01:24:02,000
Maps!

815
01:24:03,900 --> 01:24:09,700
Help! Help! Anyone, help!

816
01:24:14,800 --> 01:24:18,700
Maps! Help, it's Misty!

817
01:24:20,200 --> 01:24:23,000
Hang on, Misty!

818
01:24:23,800 --> 01:24:25,600
- What happened?
- The rip got him.

819
01:24:25,800 --> 01:24:29,100
- He fell off the rocks.
- Get help.

820
01:24:32,000 --> 01:24:34,600
You can't swim!

821
01:24:44,600 --> 01:24:46,200
[MISTY GASPING]

822
01:25:04,600 --> 01:25:06,800
Look at us. We're swimming.

823
01:25:07,000 --> 01:25:09,500
MISTY:
I'm drowning.

824
01:25:10,500 --> 01:25:12,300
Hang onto me, catch your breath.

825
01:26:39,900 --> 01:26:41,500
Shellback!

826
01:26:56,200 --> 01:26:59,100
SPARKS:
Really, we tried to save you. We did.

827
01:26:59,300 --> 01:27:01,300
SPIT:
I was trying to save you, I swear.

828
01:27:01,500 --> 01:27:03,500
I came into the water.
It was up to my neck.

829
01:27:03,700 --> 01:27:06,500
I went to the McAnsh's, and...
But then I went to Shellback.

830
01:27:06,700 --> 01:27:08,200
How you feeling, boys? Hm?

831
01:27:08,400 --> 01:27:10,600
I'm better than I was.

832
01:27:11,200 --> 01:27:12,500
I gotta say, mate...

833
01:27:12,700 --> 01:27:16,300
...you're braver than me, going out
there not knowing how to swim.

834
01:27:17,100 --> 01:27:18,900
Well done.

835
01:27:19,100 --> 01:27:21,000
SPARKS: I was just a couple of feet
away from you.

836
01:27:21,200 --> 01:27:22,700
SPIT: You were 75 yards out
or something.

837
01:27:22,900 --> 01:27:25,700
SPARKS: I could almost grab...
- Who wants some soup? Hey?

838
01:27:26,300 --> 01:27:28,200
SPARKS:
Yeah, okay.

839
01:27:29,400 --> 01:27:33,300
I might have saved you. But l...
Something just pulled me away.

840
01:27:33,800 --> 01:27:36,000
Something just pulled me.

841
01:27:36,200 --> 01:27:37,700
FEARLESS:
Come on.

842
01:27:37,900 --> 01:27:40,300
So, what do we got?

843
01:27:44,100 --> 01:27:45,500
Did you see her?

844
01:27:58,800 --> 01:28:00,900
Thanks.

845
01:28:24,600 --> 01:28:26,900
I suppose you're the one.

846
01:28:27,100 --> 01:28:28,300
You showed us all up.

847
01:28:28,500 --> 01:28:32,300
Yeah. For an old bloke,
you came through.

848
01:28:33,600 --> 01:28:36,100
I don't want to be adopted.

849
01:28:37,800 --> 01:28:39,800
SPARKS:
You don't?

850
01:28:41,300 --> 01:28:43,300
No.

851
01:28:44,700 --> 01:28:48,600
I like... Well, I like things
the way they are.

852
01:29:03,300 --> 01:29:05,000
My money's on you, Misty.

853
01:29:49,600 --> 01:29:54,300
MISTY: We were running out of time
and hope, and there was still no answer.

854
01:29:54,500 --> 01:29:57,700
No one seemed to notice
that the biggest moment of my life...

855
01:29:57,900 --> 01:30:00,200
...was about to get left behind.

856
01:30:00,300 --> 01:30:02,800
MISTY:
I'm tired of waiting.

857
01:30:09,300 --> 01:30:11,900
Come through. Come through.

858
01:30:13,900 --> 01:30:17,200
So guess you're all packed up.

859
01:30:18,200 --> 01:30:21,200
Sit down. Sit down.

860
01:30:23,700 --> 01:30:26,300
I wanna know
if you're gonna adopt me.

861
01:30:26,800 --> 01:30:29,800
I heard you tell Father Scully
you were gonna adopt one of us.

862
01:30:31,800 --> 01:30:34,400
If you're gonna adopt anyone,
it ought to be Misty.

863
01:30:34,700 --> 01:30:37,400
- Not so fast. I've got qualities.
- I can run fast.

864
01:30:37,600 --> 01:30:40,100
- You can't even stay conscious.
- Hey, boys. Boys.

865
01:30:43,000 --> 01:30:44,600
We've made up our minds.

866
01:30:52,300 --> 01:30:54,700
We wish we could adopt all of you.

867
01:30:58,400 --> 01:31:00,400
You're all such wonderful boys.

868
01:31:01,900 --> 01:31:03,500
FEARLESS:
We've put in the paperwork...

869
01:31:05,600 --> 01:31:08,400
...and it's just gonna take
a little time.

870
01:31:20,600 --> 01:31:22,900
TERESA:
Misty...

871
01:31:23,400 --> 01:31:26,400
...we want you to be our son.

872
01:31:30,300 --> 01:31:33,600
And we hope
you want us for your parents.

873
01:31:33,700 --> 01:31:36,000
We're not perfect, mate...

874
01:31:36,600 --> 01:31:39,100
...but we could love you.

875
01:31:43,300 --> 01:31:44,600
MAPS:
Good on you, mate.

876
01:31:56,700 --> 01:31:58,200
Yeah.

877
01:31:58,400 --> 01:32:01,300
Misty's the one, for sure.

878
01:32:16,900 --> 01:32:20,400
Well, hey, it's not like
we're never gonna see you again.

879
01:32:20,600 --> 01:32:22,600
I mean, we're sure
to come back and visit...

880
01:32:22,800 --> 01:32:27,400
...and if you're ever in the mood for
some boiled lamb, you can come visit us.

881
01:32:27,500 --> 01:32:30,400
FEARLESS: You boys are gonna come
back and say goodbye before you go?

882
01:32:30,500 --> 01:32:32,600
SPIT:
Oh, no worries.

883
01:32:41,600 --> 01:32:43,800
We'll see him again.

884
01:32:44,300 --> 01:32:46,100
See you, fellas.

885
01:32:49,000 --> 01:32:52,500
Just remember, Misty, no matter what,
you're still a December boy.

886
01:32:52,700 --> 01:32:54,700
Yeah.

887
01:32:55,900 --> 01:32:58,400
- Hey.
SPARKS: Got you.

888
01:32:59,000 --> 01:33:01,500
You're gonna have to run
faster than that.

889
01:33:02,000 --> 01:33:03,900
SPIT:
Hey. Whoo!

890
01:33:05,500 --> 01:33:07,800
SPARKS:
Come get me.

891
01:33:12,600 --> 01:33:14,000
SPIT:
Let's go get some souvenirs.

892
01:33:14,600 --> 01:33:17,500
Get a crab for Sister Edna.

893
01:33:18,700 --> 01:33:20,700
MAPS:
Look at this.

894
01:33:20,900 --> 01:33:24,100
Spit. Quick, before it gets away.

895
01:33:41,000 --> 01:33:43,300
MISTY:
I don't want you to be mad at me...

896
01:33:44,000 --> 01:33:46,300
...but I can't stay.

897
01:33:46,400 --> 01:33:49,000
If I was ever gonna be adopted...

898
01:33:49,100 --> 01:33:53,600
...you'd be the best parents
I could have, and that's no lie.

899
01:33:56,700 --> 01:33:59,500
But I've already got a family.

900
01:34:09,200 --> 01:34:11,000
They'd be lost without me.

901
01:34:11,200 --> 01:34:13,300
FEARLESS:
I know.

902
01:34:14,700 --> 01:34:17,000
No hard feelings?

903
01:34:17,200 --> 01:34:19,900
No hard feelings, Misty.

904
01:34:29,500 --> 01:34:31,400
Go on.

905
01:34:31,500 --> 01:34:33,500
MISTY:
Thank you.

906
01:34:33,700 --> 01:34:35,100
SPIT:
Look what I found over here.

907
01:34:35,200 --> 01:34:37,900
SPARKS: Give it back, that's mine.
SPIT: No, I found it.

908
01:34:38,100 --> 01:34:40,800
Hey, come on.

909
01:34:47,400 --> 01:34:50,300
Well, lads, this is it.

910
01:34:50,400 --> 01:34:51,900
I thought...

911
01:34:52,100 --> 01:34:56,700
...if you wanted a keepsake,
you might like to take the signal flags.

912
01:34:56,900 --> 01:34:58,700
Thanks.

913
01:35:03,300 --> 01:35:06,500
The boys would like
to say goodbye, Skipper.

914
01:35:13,900 --> 01:35:16,000
MISTY:
Thanks, Skipper.

915
01:35:18,500 --> 01:35:20,300
Thanks.

916
01:35:21,700 --> 01:35:23,500
Bless you.

917
01:35:23,600 --> 01:35:26,000
Thanks, Skipper.

918
01:35:28,800 --> 01:35:30,900
Goodbye.

919
01:35:35,700 --> 01:35:38,600
Okay, orphans, disembark.

920
01:35:38,800 --> 01:35:43,200
Left, right, left, right, left, right...

921
01:35:57,600 --> 01:35:58,600
SCULLY:
See you, Bandy.

922
01:35:58,800 --> 01:36:00,100
See you, Father.

923
01:36:00,300 --> 01:36:02,500
- See you, boys.
MAPS: Thank you, Bandy.

924
01:36:03,600 --> 01:36:04,900
MISTY: See you, Bandy.
BAND Y: Bye.

925
01:36:05,100 --> 01:36:07,300
SPARKS:
Thanks, Bandy.

926
01:36:08,300 --> 01:36:10,100
MAPS: Bye.
- Hey, look.

927
01:36:44,200 --> 01:36:49,300
MISTY: If it weren't for Maps, who knows
if any of us would have ever come back.

928
01:36:49,500 --> 01:36:51,600
We could have gone on
thinking of the Cove...

929
01:36:51,800 --> 01:36:54,200
...like one of those old postcards...

930
01:36:54,300 --> 01:36:56,500
...realer than real...

931
01:36:56,600 --> 01:36:59,900
...with each of us remembering it
however we chose.

932
01:37:12,300 --> 01:37:16,100
Coming back for the first time
after all these years...

933
01:37:16,300 --> 01:37:22,300
...fills me with a mixture of excitement
and the fear I made the whole thing up.

934
01:37:27,400 --> 01:37:32,100
Believe it or not,
Maps did become a priest...

935
01:37:32,300 --> 01:37:35,800
...traveling to Africa
to help with the refugees.

936
01:37:36,300 --> 01:37:41,200
I got his letter just a few days
before his ashes arrived.

937
01:37:45,500 --> 01:37:49,600
He told me how often
he thought about this place...

938
01:37:50,400 --> 01:37:55,000
...and how happy he was
that we could share it together.

939
01:37:55,400 --> 01:38:00,400
Maps wrote me before he went
that if anything happened...

940
01:38:01,200 --> 01:38:03,100
And here we are...

941
01:38:03,300 --> 01:38:06,200
...the December boys.

942
01:38:44,600 --> 01:38:50,300
ALL:
One, two, three, the December boys!

943
01:39:10,100 --> 01:39:12,800
SPARKS:
Hey!

944
01:39:13,300 --> 01:39:16,000
SPIT:
Maps! Hey!

945
01:39:16,200 --> 01:39:19,000
Over here!

946
01:39:19,100 --> 01:39:21,600
SPARKS:
Hey, Maps!

947
01:39:23,700 --> 01:39:26,500
See you, fellas!

948
01:44:51,000 --> 01:44:53,000
[ENGLISH SDH]

